-- "run drops stdout on panic" regression — E-STACK-OVERFLOW path, the CLEAN
-- interpreter-only guard (eval.mdk's `apply` increments a depth counter and
-- runtimePanics past evalDepthLimit, well before the real C stack would
-- exhaust).  See index_oob.mdk for the full writeup.
--
-- NOT compared against `medaka build`'s binary in the gate: the compiled
-- binary has no analogous synthetic depth counter (that is an interpreter-
-- only safety net — RUNTIME-DESIGN.md), so the SAME source instead runs
-- until the real 256 MB worker stack is exhausted and dies via the raw
-- SIGSEGV/SIGBUS fault handler.  That handler path is covered by this fix
-- too (see runtime/medaka_rt.c's mdk_flush_run_stdout_on_abort, called from
-- mdk_fault_handler / mdk_chain_previous) but is impractical to exercise
-- from a fast, portable fixture -- verified instead by a standalone C-level
-- harness against runtime/medaka_rt.c directly (see the "run drops stdout
-- on panic" fix's commit message / friction notes).
main : <IO> Unit
main =
  println "SENTINEL"
  println "\{loop 0}"

loop : Int -> Int
loop n = 1 + loop (n + 1)
